CREATE TABLE tab_disease_states (disease_state text NOT NULL CONSTRAINT tab_disease_states_pk PRIMARY KEY, display_name text NOT NULL, description text NOT NULL);
INSERT INTO tab_disease_states(disease_state,display_name,description) VALUES('CKD','Chronic Kidney Disease - No Dialysis (Malik et al, 2020)','Chronic kidney disease is renal impairment lasting at least 3 months. The disease is staged according to eGFR. Over time, multiple other body systems are also affected. To apply this disease state to an individual in PK-Sim, first select the target eGFR. Accordingly, the individual will display changes in GFR, kidney volume, kidney blood flow, plasma protein binding, hematocrit, gastric emptying time, and small intestinal transit time.

This parameterization is for individuals with CKD who are not on dialysis. It does not modify the expression or activity of enzymes or transporters - only foundational anatomy and physiology. Users should consult scientific literature for information how the relevant enzymes and transporters for their purposes may be affected.');
INSERT INTO tab_disease_states(disease_state,display_name,description) VALUES('Healthy','Healthy','Healthy individuals in PK-Sim are representative of the general population of individuals in the specified ethnicity and/or geographic area. These individuals are parameterized under the assumption that they have no chronic or comorbid disease states that would have a relevant effect on anatomy, physiology or drug disposition.');
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX tab_disease_states_description_uindex ON tab_disease_states (description);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX tab_disease_states_disease_state_uindex ON tab_disease_states (disease_state);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX tab_disease_states_display_name_uindex ON tab_disease_states (display_name);

INSERT INTO tab_parameters(parameter_name,display_name,description,dimension,default_unit) VALUES('eGFR','eGFR','Estimated GFR is the GFR normalized to body surface area (BSA). The eGFR is used clinically to determine staging of chronic kidney disease.','Flow per body surface area',NULL);
CREATE TABLE tab_population_disease_states
(
    population    text not null
        constraint tab_population_disease_states_tab_populations_population_fk
            references tab_populations
            on update cascade,
    disease_state text not null
        constraint tab_population_disease_states_tab_disease_states_disease_state_fk
            references tab_disease_states
            on update cascade,
    constraint tab_population_disease_states_pk
        primary key (population, disease_state)
);
